Terraform you can achieve
1. Manage any infrastructure
2. Track any infrastructure
3. Automate changes
4. Standardize configurations
5. Collaborate

Lifecyckle of Terraform
Write -->plan-->Apply

Commands for terraform
terraform init -- initialize the terraform provider. So whatever the confi mentione din main.tf file the provider details 
those config wll be created in localand you will be able to communicate with that provider
terraform plan
terraform apply
terraform destroy

https://github.com/iam-veeramalla/write_your_first_terraform_project
https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/tutorials/aws-get-started/install-cli

So the order is
Provider details
terraform version
region of providere
resources

Ti use/run terraform you should first configure the provider like AWS. We can configure AWS using
>>aws configure 
provide th ID;s asked for

terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 4.16"
    }
  }

//Terraform init will check for above set lo lines 
  required_version = ">= 1.2.0"    //terraform version
}

provider "aws" {
  region  = "us-west-2"
}

resource "aws_instance" "app_server" {
  ami           = "ami-830c94e3"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  tags = {
    Name = "Terraform_Demo"
  }
}

